# Vala coding standards router

Canonical rules: **`docs/coding-standards.md`**. Full checklist:
**`docs/coding-standards-router.md`** (read that file in full first).

**Top mistakes: helper methods, gratuitous line-length chopping** — inline in the
method you are editing; short `if` / `||` lines stay on one line unless genuinely
long; for format-string calls (`throw` / error-ctors / `GLib.debug`/`warning`/
`critical`) put the message on the call line (wrap remaining args grouped, not
one-per-line) (`line-length-breaking`). Task wording is not approval for helpers
(`method-names-new-methods`).

## Step 1 — Before the first Vala edit

1. Read **`docs/coding-standards-router.md`** in full.
2. **Universal:** read every section in the universal table (grep `section: <slug>`).
3. **Scenario:** add slugs for every **yes** in the scenario table.
4. Read each slug’s full block in `docs/coding-standards.md`.
5. If `docblocks` is in your set, read **`docs/code-documentation.md`** in full.

### Universal — read before edit, re-scan diff before done

| Did your change (or will it)…? | Section slug |
|--------------------------------|--------------|
| Declare a **local** or **loop** variable? | `temporary-variables` — **`var` only**; not `string x =` |
| Access instance fields/properties/methods? | `this-prefix` |
| Add/change `if` / `else` / nested branches? | `reducing-nesting` |
| Compare enums with `if (a \|\| b)`? | `switch-case` |
| Add null checks or redundant guards? | `defensive-code-null-checks` |
| Use `??` or default a nullable value? | `null-coalescing` |
| Tempted to add a **helper method**? | `method-names-new-methods` — **inline** unless user/plan named it |
| Add new `const` / named constant? | `method-names-new-methods` — use literal at use site |

**STOP before done if:** explicit type on a local, missing `this.`, **added a helper**, **new const**, **chopped a short line**, gratuitous `else`, enum `||` chain, or skipped `agent-compliance-gate`.

### Scenario checklist (yes → add slug(s))

See **`docs/coding-standards-router.md`** — every row in the scenario table.

## Step 2 — Before marking done

1. Re-read section `agent-compliance-gate`.
2. Re-run the universal “STOP if you…” column on your diff.
3. Search changed files:

```bash
rg '^\s+(string|int|bool|uint|int64|float|double)\s+\w+\s*[=;]' --glob '*.vala' <files>
```

Partial compliance is a violation.
